    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>A natural, solid, hydrocarbon substance, distinguishable from bitumen by being infusible and insoluble. When heated, however, pyrobitumens generate or transform into bitumen-like liquid or gaseous petroleum compounds. This class of natural bituminous material includes peat, lignite, and coal.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
